\displaystyle\left|\frac{1}{x} - \frac{1}{y}\right|
\lim_{(x,y)\to\infty}\left|\frac{1}{x}-\frac{1}{y}\right|=0
x,y
x
\lim_{ x \to\infty} \frac{1}{|x|} =0 \tag{1}
\lim_{ (x,y) \to\infty} \frac{1}{|x|} =0 \tag{2} 
\lim_{ (x,y) \to\infty} \frac{1}{|y|} =0 \tag{3} 
\lim_{(x,y)\to\infty}\left|\frac{1}{x}\right|+\left|\frac{1}{y}\right|=0
0\le \left|\frac{1}{x}-\frac{1}{y}\right|\le \left|\frac{1}{x}\right|+\left|\frac{1}{y}\right|
